Dootix, named after Sanskrit word doot (messenger) is a 64-bit hobby OS kernel targeting x86_64 platforms, built from scratch for practice, educational, and personal research purposes.

Current Version
	- 0.1.0 - early bootable kernel

Current Status
	- Multiboot2 boot via GRUB
	- Long Mode enabled
	- VGA text console
	- Serial logging
	- IDT and basic IRQ handling

The system is still under development, hence a few unfinished subsystems

Build
	- x86_64-elf-gcc
	- x86_64-elf-ld
	- QEMU
	- GRUB

Build & Run
```bash
make
qemu-system-x86_64 -cdrom dootix.iso 
